	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Apparently it also relies on your DAC using sample-and-hold (i.e. unfiltered at the very least), which rules out most outputs. This makes the output quickly change levels (higher harmonics = sharper waves), which apparently several of the patterns rely on. So the fact that it's a wav is kind of misleading.

		

